API Automation Capstone Project
1) Project Setup
Create project environment and declare all necessary variables with corresponding values.

2) GET – Retrieve All Objects
Endpoint: https://api.restful-api.dev/objects

Positive Test Scenario

Print all object details with names containing the word "Apple" on Rest Assured console.

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 200

Print object details (id & name) containing "Apple"

3) GET – Query Parameters
Endpoint: https://api.restful-api.dev/objects?id=3&id=5&id=10

Positive Test Scenario

Retrieve object details based on ids passed as query params (?id=3&id=5&id=10).

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 200

Response body should contain all object ids and names for 3, 5, 10

4) GET – Path Parameter
Endpoint: https://api.restful-api.dev/objects/:id

Negative Test Scenario

Request object details for invalid id (7555).

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 404

Response body should contain error message:

json
{ "error": "Object with id = 7555 was not found." }
Positive Test Scenario

Request object details for valid id (7).

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 200

Response body should contain object detail:

json
{
  "id": "7",
  "name": "Apple MacBook Pro 16",
  "data": {
    "year": 2019,
    "price": 1849.99,
    "CPU model": "Intel Core i9",
    "Hard disk size": "1 TB"
  }
}
5) POST – Create Object
Endpoint: https://api.restful-api.dev/objects

Positive Test Scenario

Add object details using appropriate JSON payload.

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 200

Response body should contain added object detail with fields:

id

name

createdAt timestamp

6) PATCH – Update Object
Endpoint: https://api.restful-api.dev/objects/:id

Negative Test Scenario

Update object details for invalid id (random value).

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 404

Response body should contain error message:

json
{ "error": "No object with id = 7566 doesn't exist." }
Positive Test Scenario

Update object details for valid id (generated in POST request).

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 200

Response body should contain updated object detail with fields:

id

name

updatedAt timestamp

7) DELETE – Remove Object
Endpoint: https://api.restful-api.dev/objects/:id

Negative Test Scenario

Delete object details for invalid id (444).

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 404

Response body should contain error message:

json
{ "error": "No object with id = 444 doesn't exist." }
Positive Test Scenario

Delete object details for valid id (generated in POST request).

Assertions:

HTTP response status code = 200

Response body should contain success message:

json
{ "message": "Object with id = 1234 has been deleted." }
